-- Thai Rice Farmers Told to Delay Planting to End of July on Lack of Rain
-- Supunnabul Suwannakij
-- 2010-06-23T03:28:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/thai-rice-farmers-told-to-delay-planting-to-end-of-july-on-lack-of-rain.html

          
          
             The Thai government told farmers to
delay planting by another month to the end of July because of
delayed rains and warned of possible crop damage from flooding
in September and October, according to an announcement by the
Meteorological Department.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
